Which sentence is written correctly? (a) David and Maria negotiated the price of theirs new car. (b) The weather changed suddenly, and Carlos ran to the car to get her umbrella. (c) A local newspaper reporter wrote an article about her neighbor's new business. (d) A meteor lit up the night sky over him's town and landed in a field near my house.

The verbal exchange where Unferth challenges Beowulf by telling the story of the battle with Breca C. The fight between Beowulf and Grendel when Grendel loses his arm D. The meeting between Beowulf and the Scylding coast guard when the ship arrives at shore
